    <h1>Installing the CLI on Linux</h1>
  </div>
  <br/>
  <section>
<pre>
<code class="lang-bash">sudo su
curl -L http://hootcode.com/downloads/hootcode > /usr/local/bin/hootcode; chmod +x /usr/local/bin/hootcode </code>
</pre>

<div class="alert alert-danger">
  <p> <i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Read it before you run it, people.</p>
</div>
<p>By default, the installer will try to put it in <code>/usr/local/bin/</code> or <code>$HOME/bin/</code>.</p>
<p>If you'd like it to live somewhere else, you can specify it up front:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">DIR=/path/to/bin ./install</code></pre>
<p>One more step ahead to get Hootcode configured. Here is the configuration <a href="/onboarding/install-cli">link </a> <p>
  </section>
  <b>Note: </b> Test whether hootcode installed successfully or not by typing the command <b> "hootcode -v" </b>
